<p>Then, we decided to check out lower Yosemite falls. With a low water season, not as spectacular as always, but beautiful nonetheless.
<img src="/assets/images/dew/falls.jpg" alt="" width="500" /><br />
<span class="caption italic"></span>
On the way back to the car, we were delighted to spot a wild black bear munching on some berries!</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/dew/bear.jpg" alt="" width="600" /><br />
<span class="caption italic"></span></p>

<p>It was a successful first day. The next morning we set off to the McGurk Meadows trailhead. After a few miles, we arrived
at the meadow.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/dew/meadow.jpg" alt="Mia and some pretty wildflowers" width="500" /><br />
<span class="caption italic">Mia and some pretty wildflowers</span></p>

<p>A few more brutal miles uphill, and we were rewarded with this view from Dewey point.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/dew/dewey1.JPEG" alt="El Capitan on the left" width="600" /><br />
